{"lemma":"مُرَتَّبَةٍ","slug":"مُرَتَّبَةٍ","root":"ر.ت.ب","root_slug":"ر-ت-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ت-ب","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["adj","noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14672"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%AA%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"arranger, consolidator"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"typesetter, compositor"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"arranged, consolidated"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"regular"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"ready"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"salary, wages","examples":[{"text":"وبهذا المسجد جماعة من الطلبة يتعلمون العلم ولهم مرتبات من مال المسجد، وله مطبخة يصنع فيها الطعام للوارد والصادر ولإطعام الفقراء من المسلمين بها.","english":"In this mosque also there are a number of students of religious science who receive stipends from its revenue, and it has a kitchen from which all travellers and the poor Muslims of the town are supplied with food."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"regular supplies","tags":["in-plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the active participle of رَتَّبَ (rattaba, “to arrange, to fix a salary for”).\n\nDerived from the passive participle of رَتَّبَ (rattaba, “to arrange, to fix a salary for”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14672","headword_ar":"مَرْتَبَةٌ","root":"rtb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", and its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAtibu","text_ar":"مَرَاتِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rutobapN","text_ar":"رُتْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in six places. ―         -b2-  Accord. to As, it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of observation, which is the summit of a mountain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the upper part thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) accord. to Kh, (S,) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maraAtib","text_ar":"مَرَاتِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"in mountains and in deserts ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaHaArK","text_ar":"صَحَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":") are ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"structures such as are termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaAm","text_ar":"اَعْلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalamN","text_ar":"عَلَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which are stationed"},{"kind":"text","text":"(↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"turabu","text_ar":"تُرَبُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scouts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"places to which scouts ascend, in,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon, mountains."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b3-  The pl. also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Narrow and rugged parts of valleys."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA from a trad.) ―         -b4-  And the sing.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Any difficult station"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"position."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ratabN","text_ar":"رَتَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places. ―         -b6-  [In post-classical works, and in the language of the present day, it is applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mattress, upon which to sit or recline or lie; such as is spread upon a couch-frame or upon the ground."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"}],"source_refs":["S","T"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}